# bot-trading (Cursor)

This rule **always applies** in Agent chat. It does not apply to Tab or inline edit ([Cursor rules](https://cursor.com/docs/rules)).

## Read order

1. Repo root [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md)
2. [`notes/reference/index.md`](../../notes/reference/index.md) when you need contracts or depth
3. [`trading_bot/AGENTS.md`](../../trading_bot/AGENTS.md) when touching `trading_bot/`

## Safety and verification

Entries, exits, and capital are safety-critical. Treat strategy claims as unverified until checked against [`notes/reference/strategy.md`](../../notes/reference/strategy.md) and the matching engine code.

## Repo boundaries

| Area | Location |
|------|-----------|
| Prisma schema | `trading_bot/backend/prisma/schema.prisma` — **no** checked-in migration workflow |
| SQL views | `trading_bot/backend/prisma/views/create_views.sql` |
| Providers | `trading_bot/backend/src/services/` |
| Browser → backend writes | `trading_bot/dashboard/app/api/[...path]/route.ts` |

Use **relative paths** in committed code and docs.

## Changes and docs

Prefer the smallest correct change. When contracts or runtime behavior change, update the owning note under `notes/reference/` in the same pass when this repo expects that pairing.

Do not add or expand comments in TS/TSX/JS unless you are only editing text inside an existing comment the file already relied on.

## MCP and skills

- Tool choice and defaults: [`notes/reference/tool-routing.md`](../../notes/reference/tool-routing.md)
- Cursor loads [`.cursor/mcp.json`](../../.cursor/mcp.json). Keep `mcpServers` **keys** aligned with repo root [`.mcp.json`](../../.mcp.json); then run `node scripts/claude-harness/validate-mcp.mjs` (see [`.cursor/README.md`](../../.cursor/README.md)).
- Skills: [`.agents/skills/`](../../.agents/skills/) — when a task matches a skill’s `description`, read that `SKILL.md` first. After skill edits: `node scripts/claude-harness/lint-skills.mjs`.
